1. Forgotten Root Password
Solution:
1.	Boot into GRUB menu.
2.	Edit the boot entry by pressing e.
3.	Append init=/bin/bash to the kernel line.
4.	Boot with Ctrl+X.
5.	Mount the root filesystem: mount -o remount,rw /.
6.	Reset password: passwd root.
7.	Reboot: exec /sbin/init.
________________________________________
2. System Fails to Boot
Solution:
1.	Boot into rescue mode or live CD.
2.	Check boot logs: journalctl -xb.
3.	Verify bootloader configuration: cat /boot/grub/grub.cfg.
4.	Repair GRUB: grub-install /dev/sdX and update-grub.
5.	Check for disk errors: fsck /dev/sdXY.
________________________________________
3. Disk Space Full
Solution:
1.	Identify usage: df -h and du -sh /path/*.
2.	Remove unnecessary files: rm -rf /path/to/files.
3.	Clear package cache: apt clean or yum clean all.
4.	Check logs: truncate -s 0 /var/log/filename.
________________________________________
4. Network Connectivity Issues
Solution:
1.	Check interface status: ip addr.
2.	Restart network service: systemctl restart NetworkManager or service networking restart.
3.	Test connectivity: ping 8.8.8.8.
4.	Verify DNS: cat /etc/resolv.conf.
5.	Check firewall rules: iptables -L or ufw status.
________________________________________
5. Permission Denied Errors
Solution:
1.	Check file permissions: ls -l /path/to/file.
2.	Change permissions: chmod 755 /path/to/file.
3.	Verify ownership: chown user:group /path/to/file.
________________________________________
6. Unable to Install Packages
Solution:
1.	Update repositories: apt update or yum makecache.
2.	Fix broken dependencies: apt --fix-broken install.
3.	Clean cache: rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/* and retry.
________________________________________
7. Slow System Performance
Solution:
1.	Check CPU usage: top or htop.
2.	Identify memory hogs: free -h or vmstat.
3.	Stop unnecessary services: systemctl stop service_name.
4.	Clear cache: sync; echo 3 > /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches.
________________________________________
8. Kernel Panic
Solution:
1.	Reboot into a previous kernel from GRUB.
2.	Update or reinstall the kernel: apt install --reinstall linux-image-version.
3.	Check hardware logs: dmesg.
________________________________________
9. X Server Fails to Start
Solution:
1.	Check logs: cat /var/log/Xorg.0.log.
2.	Reconfigure X server: dpkg-reconfigure xserver-xorg.
3.	Verify drivers: lsmod | grep driver_name.
________________________________________
10. SSH Connection Issues
Solution:
1.	Verify service: systemctl status sshd.
2.	Check port: netstat -tuln | grep 22.
3.	Restart SSH: systemctl restart sshd.
4.	Verify firewall: ufw allow 22.
________________________________________
11. File System Corruption
Solution:
1.	Boot into rescue mode.
2.	Run fsck /dev/sdXY.
3.	Reboot after repairs.
________________________________________
12. Application Crashes
Solution:
1.	Check logs: journalctl -xe or cat /var/log/application.log.
2.	Restart application: systemctl restart app_name.
3.	Update software: apt upgrade app_name.
________________________________________
13. High Load Average
Solution:
1.	Check processes: top or uptime.
2.	Kill resource hogs: kill -9 PID.
3.	Optimize services: Adjust configurations for high-demand services.
________________________________________
14. Unresponsive System
Solution:
1.	Switch to TTY: Ctrl+Alt+F2.
2.	Kill processes: killall process_name.
3.	Reboot: reboot.
________________________________________
15. Corrupted Configuration Files
Solution:
1.	Backup file: cp /etc/config /etc/config.bak.
2.	Restore default: Refer to the package documentation.
________________________________________
16. Mounting Issues
Solution:
1.	Check mount points: mount or lsblk.
2.	Mount manually: mount /dev/sdXY /mnt.
3.	Update /etc/fstab if persistent mounting is needed.
________________________________________
17. Time Synchronization Issues
Solution:
1.	Install NTP: apt install ntp.
2.	Sync time: ntpdate pool.ntp.org.
3.	Enable service: systemctl enable ntpd.
________________________________________
18. Hardware Not Detected
Solution:
1.	Check hardware: lspci or lsusb.
2.	Install drivers: apt install firmware-linux.
________________________________________
19. Library Dependency Errors
Solution:
1.	Check missing libraries: ldd /path/to/binary.
2.	Install dependencies: apt install lib_name.
________________________________________
20. Firewall Misconfigurations
Solution:
1.	View rules: iptables -L or ufw status.
2.	Adjust rules: iptables -A or ufw allow port.
________________________________________
21. Cron Jobs Not Running
Solution:
1.	Verify syntax: crontab -l.
2.	Check logs: cat /var/log/syslog | grep CRON.
________________________________________
22. SELinux Denials
Solution:
1.	Check logs: cat /var/log/audit/audit.log.
2.	Allow rules: setsebool -P boolean_name 1.
________________________________________
23. Outdated Kernel
Solution:
1.	Update kernel: apt install linux-image-version.
2.	Reboot and verify: uname -r.
________________________________________
24. Unable to Unmount Device
Solution:
1.	Check usage: lsof /mnt/point.
2.	Kill processes: kill -9 PID.
3.	Unmount: umount /mnt/point.
________________________________________
25. Package Manager Lock
Solution:
1.	Remove lock files: rm /var/lib/dpkg/lock.
2.	Reconfigure: dpkg --configure -a.
________________________________________
26. DNS Resolution Issues
Solution:
1.	Test DNS: dig domain.com.
2.	Update /etc/resolv.conf with correct nameservers.
________________________________________
27. Stuck Processes
Solution:
1.	Identify process: ps aux | grep process_name.
2.	Kill process: kill -9 PID.
________________________________________
28. USB Device Not Recognized
Solution:
1.	Check device: lsusb.
2.	Reload USB modules: modprobe -r usb_storage && modprobe usb_storage.
________________________________________
29. Kernel Module Issues
Solution:
1.	Load module: modprobe module_name.
2.	Check logs: dmesg | grep module_name.
________________________________________
30. Logs Filling Up Disk
Solution:
1.	Truncate logs: truncate -s 0 /var/log/filename.
2.	Configure log rotation: /etc/logrotate.conf.

